         <a href=\"Blog/Post?id=138\">\n                        Superfighters Deluxe Alpha 1.2.1</a>\n                </h2>\n                <span class=\"blogCreateDate\">Added 1 Mar 2017\n                    \n                </span>\n                <br>\n                <ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tNew weapon: C4.\n\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\tYou can only carry one at a time.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\tAfter you throw it you get a detonator.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\tDoes not explode when shot, but can be set off by explosions.</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tScriptAPI: System.Text.RegularExpressions namespace is now available.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tMinor fixes and tweaks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n            \n                <p>\n                    <img src=\"Images/MythoSkullSmall.png\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n                </p>\n            \n                <h2 class=\"blogHeading\">\n                    <a href=\"Blog/Post?id=137\">\n                        Superfighters Deluxe Alpha 1.2.0b</a>\n                </h2>\n                <span class=\"blogCreateDate\">Added 20 Feb 2017\n                    \n                </span>\n                <br>\n                <ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed a bug where the 3-hit combo caused increased knockback on grabbed players.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed bugs related to player positioning and rotation while caught in a dive.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tMore accurate magazine spawn positions when reloading guns.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tWhen throwing a grabbed player, your own velocity is added to the thrown player's velocity (when you are standing on a moving object for instance).</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tOther minor fixes and tweaksies.</li>\n</ul>\n\n            \n                <p>\n                    <img src=\"Images/MythoSkullSmall.png\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n                </p>\n            \n                <h2 class=\"blogHeading\">\n                    <a href=\"Blog/Post?id=136\">\n                        Superfighters Deluxe Alpha 1.2.0</a>\n                </h2>\n                <span class=\"blogCreateDate\">Added 18 Feb 2017\n                    \n                </span>\n                <br>\n                <p>\n\t<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://mythologicinteractive.com/Data/SpeechBubble.jpg\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 296px;\"></p>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tUpdated Tutorial.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tUpdated Template map.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tNew items: Helmet 2, Fedora 2, Dog Tag.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tYou can now start the server software from the launcher.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tToggle-throwing-mode is now prioritized over attacking, so pressing toggle-throwing-mode mid-combo will abort the combo.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tToggle throwing mode is now queued properly while throwing a grabbed player.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tToggling throwing mode during sprint-jumps no longer slows you down.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tCharging a throw (priming a mine/grenade/molotov) during sprint-jumps no longer slows you down.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tOptional \"-start\" command line argument added that will auto start the game/server. Now possible to autostart the server with command \"'Superfighters Deluxe.exe' -start -server\" which can be added to autorun programs if you want.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tUpdated the main font so that \"I\" and \"l\" are no longer identical (to prevent account name impersonation).</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded sound and screen shake effect to the pistons on the Pistons map.</li>\n</ul>\n<div>\n\tMap Editor:</div>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded multi-edit support: you can now see and edit the common properties of multiple selected tiles at once.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tNew start option added to be able to test a map using 0 to 8 players. Toggle control between characters by pressing Shift+F1 to Shift+F8.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tNew PlayerCommandTrigger to let players perform scripted actions. See the in-editor help for more details.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tNew DialogueTrigger to display speech bubbles with text. This is a work-in-progress.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tImproved PlayerSpawnMarkers with more options to customize how the player will spawn. See the in-editor help for more details.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tImproved PlayerSpawnTrigger with options for startup throwables and powerup items and initial team.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded PlayerInputEnableTrigger to be able to enable/disable player input for a specific player.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded PlayerModifierInfo to be able to modify certain properties for individual players.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded PlayerTerminateTrigger to be used to remove/gib or kill players spawned from PlayerSpawnTrigger/PlayerSpawnMarkers.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tOnDeathPlayerTrigger can now be filtered on a specific player directly in the editor.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAreaTriggers can now be filtered on specific objects and players directly in the editor.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tThe map editor now caches certain editor content. Subsequent startups will be faster.</li>\n</ul>\n<div>\n\t<div>\n\t\tScriptAPI:</div>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded Game.CreateDialogue(), Game.GetDialogues() to be able to manage dialogues.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IPlayer.AddCommandAction(), IPlayer.ClearCommandQueue(), IPlayer.PerformedCommandCount, IPlayer.CurrentCommandIndex and IPlayer.TotalCommandCount to be able to manage player commands.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tIPlayer.RunToPosition() is obsolete (and will be removed in future versions) and replaced with player command 'MoveToPosition'.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tIPlayer.SetBotType(), IPlayer.BotType is obsolete (and will be removed in future versions) and replaced with the new concept \"BotBehavior\" which will control how a bot will behave.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IPlayer.SetBotBehavior() and IPlayer.GetBotBehavior() to control how the AI should control the player (these are placeholder functions and can only activate the old BotType.TutorialA atm).</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IPlayer.IsAIControlled property to get if the IPlayer is currently controlled by the AI.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IPlayerStatistics.TotalShotsFired, TotalItemsThrown, TotalPlayersThrown, TotalReloads, TotalEmptyGunsFireAttemts.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IObject.GetMaxHealth() to be able to read maximum health of an object.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded OnShutdown() that's always run with signature \"public void OnShutdown()\" in scripts before a map restart or when a script is stopped. Store some final information to Game.Data if needed here.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAfterStartup() is now run for scripts started mid-game as well.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tOnStartup() is now run before triggers that activate on startup. AfterStartup() is now run after triggers that activate on startup. OnShutdown() is run before a map restart or before a script is stopped.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tGame.RunCommand() can now run any command from extension scripts.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded User.Ping property to read current ping.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IPlayer.SetModifiers(), IPlayer.GetModifiers(), IPlayer.ClearModifiers() to be able to change modifiers for players.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tUpdated IPlayer.SetProfile(), IPlayer.GetProfile() to be able to change profile for players.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tObjectPlayerSpawnTriggers can now be fully changed via the ScriptAPI.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tThe OnPlayerDeathEvent can now bring players back to life by calling SetHealth with a value higher than 0.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IObjectOnDestroyTrigger.Reset() to reset the destroyed counter and \"re-active\" the trigger.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tAdded IObject.GetMaxHealth() and updated summary on IObject.SetMaxHealth(value).</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t<div>\n\t\tBug fixes:</div>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where thrown items going through portals would hit players located anywhere between the portals.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where holding both direction keys while rocket riding caused the rocket on other clients to act crazy.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug in map \"Pistons\" where players sometimes wouldn't be gibbed properly in the machines.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where you could select template maps with the /map command.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where you could get knocked down by jumping over recently thrown players.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bunch of bugs related to the moderator list and ban list handling.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug that caused a little bit of energy to be drained while standing still when pressing toggle-sprint (default Shift).</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where you couldn't whisper to people from the server software.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where the camera would keep shaking after a map transition.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tFixed a bug where the player's name could be white in the scoreboard even when not logged in.</li>\n\t\t<li>\n\t\t\tOther fixes and tweaks.</li>\n\t</ul>\n</div>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>\n\n            \n                <p>\n                    <img  <a href=\"Blog/Post?id=135\">\n                        Superfighters Deluxe Alpha 1.1.1b</a>\n                </h2>\n                <span class=\"blogCreateDate\">Added 18 Nov 2016\n                    \n                </span>\n                <br>\n                <ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed a bug where you could get stuck while grab-charging after a roll.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed command /SCRIPTS not working correctly for the host when moderator commands were limited to a subset of commands.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed command /STOPSCRIPT showing incorrect error message when trying to stop a script that can't be found.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tSome more debris tiles have been made available in the map editor.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tSome fixes to the launcher.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tOther fixes and tweaks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n            \n                <p>\n                    <img src=\"Images/MythoSkullSmall.png\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n                </p>\n            \n                <h2 class=\"blogHeading\">\n                    <a href=\"Blog/Post?id=134\">\n                        Superfighters Deluxe Alpha 1.1.1</a>\n                </h2>\n                <span class=\"blogCreateDate\">Added 12 Nov 2016\n                    \n                </span>\n                <br>\n                <ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tYou can now walk while grabbing a dead player.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tMade it easier to grab dead players that are slightly below you.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tPlayers now rotate the right way after being thrown from a grab.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed a bug where you could grab instantly after blocking an attack, letting you perform a grab between your opponent's attacks.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tFixed a bug where grabbed players could be automatically dropped if grabbed against a wall.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tSome optimizations.</li>\n</ul>\n<div>\n\tServer Software</div>\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAccount names now visible.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tCommands and whispers are now visible in the chat log.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded option to periodically save the chat log to file. See the help for more details.</li>\n\t<li>\n\t\tAdded possibility to control which commands moderators can use via config.ini file.
